> Module Eligibility

# Synthetic Eligibility Program

## Declarations

```catala-metadata
declaration structure Household:
  data monthly_gross_income content money
  data size content integer
  data has_elderly_member content boolean
  data countable_resources content money

declaration scope Eligibility:
  input household content Household
  internal federal_poverty_line content money
  internal income_test_passes condition
  internal elderly_test_passes condition
  internal resource_disqualification condition
  output is_eligible condition
```

## Federal poverty line by household size

*Source: policy.md — Section 1. Definitions*

```catala
scope Eligibility:
  definition federal_poverty_line equals
    if household.size = 1 then $1,255
    else if household.size = 2 then $1,704
    else $1,704 + (decimal of (household.size - 2)) * $448
```

## Income eligibility threshold

*Source: policy.md — Section 2. Income eligibility threshold*

```catala
scope Eligibility:
  rule income_test_passes
    under condition household.monthly_gross_income < federal_poverty_line * 200%
    consequence fulfilled
```

## Categorical eligibility for elderly households

*Source: policy.md — Section 3. Categorical eligibility for elderly households*

```catala
scope Eligibility:
  rule elderly_test_passes
    under condition household.has_elderly_member
    consequence fulfilled
```

## Resource disqualification

*Source: policy.md — Section 4. Disqualification — assets exceeding limit*

```catala
scope Eligibility:
  rule resource_disqualification
    under condition household.countable_resources > $5,000
    consequence fulfilled
```

## Final eligibility decision

*Source: policy.md — Section 5. Final eligibility decision*

```catala
scope Eligibility:
  rule is_eligible
    under condition
      (income_test_passes or elderly_test_passes)
      and not resource_disqualification
    consequence fulfilled
```
